# Nexus
Nexus Artifactory Repository Installation
===========================================

# Nexus Server Installation in AWS Ec2 Instance:

# Pre Requisite Software: 
	- Java is the pre requisite software for Nexus Server. 
	- $ java -version
	 1.8 

# Hardware Requirements:
	- Nexus Server requires at least 2GB RAM. [Better to have 4GB RAM]

$ free -h
  ## Login as as root user
	- $ su - root  / $ sudo -i
    
To downlode the nexus:
$ cd /opt
$ mkdir nexus [To create a Dir]
$ cd nexus
$ sudo wget https://download.sonatype.com/nexus/3/latest-unix.tar.gz

# Extract the Nexus software
opt$ tar -xvzf  nexus-3.15.2.01-unix.tar.gz

$ mv nexus-3.15.2-01  nexus   (Renamed it)
## As a good security practice, Nexus is not advised to run as nexus Service as a root,  new user called nexus and grant sudo access to manage nexus services as follows: 

Create a user for the nexus:
$ useradd nexus
$ passwd nexus

## Give the sudo access to the nexus user:
$ visudo    (Give sudo access to the any normal user for the best practice)
nexus     ALL=(ALL) 		NOPASSWD:    ALL

## Then we have to change the owner and group permissions to nexus  and   /opt/sonatype-work  dir:
$ chown  -R  nexus:nexus  nexus
$ chown  -R  nexus:nexus  sonatype-work

## Then also change the directory permissions for that user:
$ chmod -R 775 nexus
$ chmod -R 775 sonatype-work

## Open the /opt/nexus/bin/nexus.rc  file,[  uncomment   run_as_user="nexus"  parameter and set as nexus user]
$ vim  /opt/nexus/bin/nexus.rc
run_as_user="nexus"

## Add nexus as a service at boot time  (Create softlink for that)
$ ln -s /opt/nexus/bin/nexus  /etc/init.d/nexus

## Switch as a nexus user and start the nexus service as follows:
$ su - nexus

## Enable the nexus service: 
$ sudo systemctl  enable  nexus  (When system reboot load it will automatically start the service)
$ sudo systemctl  start  nexus 
$ sudo systemctl status nexus
$ sudo systemctl restart nexus
$ sudo systemctl stop nexus
